<sections><clause id="_28e3b3df-11cb-49ff-9623-83fb41b21434" unnumbered="true" obligation="normative" displayorder="1">

<p id="_c74042fe-8861-4425-8b67-b094cbfebaf4">
<strong>HeNe laser operating on the <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mn>3</mn><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></stem> transition</strong>
</p>
</clause>
<clause id="_cipm_recommended_value_of_the_frequency" obligation="normative" displayorder="2"><title depth="1">1.<tab/>CIPM recommended value <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ci2007" citeas="[1]">[1]</eref> of the frequency</title><p id="_63b04551-79e6-4247-96c2-a8bfdb35a7af">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>H</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>N</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>unstabilised</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>473.612&#8239;7</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_THz"><mi mathvariant="normal">THz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>
</p>
<p id="_5ba70246-c4e6-4807-a0ce-5b6213dd9059">equivalent to</p>
<p id="_cf92c7cd-22c8-4d93-ba22-5e083f1dfd0d">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>H</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>N</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>unstabilised</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>632.990&#8239;8</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_nm"><mi mathvariant="normal">nm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>
</p>
<p id="_9195ad82-550e-45bc-983d-ffff5880b311">with a relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1.5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem> applies apply to the radiation in vacuum of an unstabilized helium-neon laser operating solely on the <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mn>3</mn><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></stem> transition, independent of the isotopic mixture of the neon.</p>
<p id="_a89a7191-f7a2-4386-b785-2c7edb903058">
<strong>This wavelength (in vacuum) value was also recommended by CIPM 2007 as a Realization of the Definition of the Metre</strong>
</p></clause>
<clause id="_source_data" obligation="normative" displayorder="3">
<title depth="1">2.<tab/>Source data</title>
<p id="_de0955cd-ad35-4fa9-b90b-9832908470a3">The source data are derived from an investigation carried out by the CCL and published in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="stone" citeas="[2]">[2]</eref></p>
</clause>
